body:
Can you check the `spark-sql_2.12-3.2.0.jar` in the classpath of Databricks runtime? If it's present, you can unarchive to some dir and inspect the method as follows:
```
jar xvf /path/to/jars/spark-sql_2.12-3.2.0.jar

find . -name '*FileStatusCache.class' | xargs javap -p > classes.txt

cat classes.txt
```

This is what I see in my local:
```
public abstract class org.apache.spark.sql.execution.datasources.FileStatusCache {
  public static void resetForTesting();
  public static org.apache.spark.sql.execution.datasources.FileStatusCache getOrCreate(org.apache.spark.sql.SparkSession);
  public scala.Option<org.apache.hadoop.fs.FileStatus[]> getLeafFiles(org.apache.hadoop.fs.Path);
  public abstract void putLeafFiles(org.apache.hadoop.fs.Path, org.apache.hadoop.fs.FileStatus[]);
  public abstract void invalidateAll();
  public org.apache.spark.sql.execution.datasources.FileStatusCache();
}
```
You can see the signature of `putLeafFiles` method and it is same as that in Apache Spark 3.1.2.
